ArcelorMittal Holds Talks About Investing in Guinea, RTG Says

-- B y   O u g n a   C a m a r a
-- 
2011-02-28T11:15:17Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-28/arcelormittal-holds-talks-with-guinea-officials-about-investment-rtg-says.html
  ArcelorMittal , the world’s largest
steelmaker, held talks with the government of  Guinea  about the
possibility of investing in the African nation, Radio Television
Guineenne reported, without saying where it got the information.  Prime Minister Mohamed Said Fofana held talks with Sudhir Maheshwari, executive vice president at the steelmaker, the
state-owned news agency said. It didn’t give any further
details.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ougna Camara in Conakry via Accra at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at   asguazzin@bloomberg.net  